## Description
The&nbsp;**Compose Documents**&nbsp;task allows to&nbsp;generate documents using Infinica templates.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Project &gt;&nbsp;Resource** field and select the Document Template resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see:&nbsp;[Document Template Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/document-template-resource-reference).

- In the **Input** section, fill in the required fields:

In the **Pattern**&nbsp;field, enter the filename pattern in glob format (for example, **.xml*).

- In the&nbsp;**Document** field, enter the path to the Document element.

- In the&nbsp;**Output** section, fill in the required fields:

Select the&nbsp;**Format** of the output file. The available options are:

**PDF**

- **FOP**

> Note

The FOP format corresponds to the Doxee Platform 2 "XML embedded IF" format.

- In the&nbsp;**Filename** field, enter the name of the output file to produce.
